# JAX / RL performance (Orbit Wars)

Adapted from [cursorrules-collection `practices/performance.mdc`](https://github.com/nedcodes-ok/cursorrules-collection/blob/main/rules-mdc/practices/performance.mdc) — web/DB sections omitted.

## Measure before optimizing

- Profile rollouts/training (update timing in `logs/*_jax.jsonl`, `ow benchmark training`) before micro-optimizing Python.
- Document before/after: env-steps/s or wall time per update — not “should be faster.”
- Launch-hygiene gates use calibrated baselines (`docs/benchmarks/launch-hygiene-e2e-baseline.json`); do not invent thresholds.

## JAX-specific

- Treat JIT compile as a cost: avoid reshaping/retracing in hot paths (`src/jax/rollout/collect.py`, `ppo_update.py`).
- Prefer structural changes in `conf/` + one compile-friendly path over many Python branches inside `jax.lax.scan`.
- Metric merges use `_merge_metric_dicts` inside scans; finalize rates after the scan (rollout invariant).

## GPU / process hygiene

- One heavy GPU job at a time (train, calibration, Gate 5); check terminals before starting.
- Do not pipe long `ow train` / gate output through `tail`/`head` — progress on stderr; use `ow runs watch` or `tail -f` on `logs/*_jax.jsonl`.

## When not to optimize

- Do not weaken preflight/tournament floors in `docs/benchmarks/preflight-calibration.json` to make a run pass.
- Confirm metric denominators before gating (`overall_win_rate` vs noop-only, `binary_win` reward vs win rate).
